An airport allows a city to produce veteran air units.  This includes helicopters.  Damaged air units which stay in a city for one full turn without moving are completely restored.  Two cities with airports can airlift one unit per turn.  Airlifting instantly transports the unit from one city to another.  Airlifting  uses up all of a unit's movement points.  A unit must have some movement points left to be airlifted.  Building an airport requires having the Radio technology.  It costs 120 to build an airport.  Airports have an upkeep of 3.
